dspace.title: (OAR) Google Scholar does not index most publicly available items

comments.body: Google seems to only offer further support using https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/1249981?hl=en&ref_topic=9002753, I'm going to attempt to contact support using less direct routes.

Attempting to access the admin. suite for Google services is blocked for both my NetID, and the `oar@princeton.edu` accounts:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/68423323-e26ccc00-016f-11ea-8fe0-a084ce9c33c2.png)
There appears to be another Gmail account, `oarprinceton@gmail.com` which I may be able to use, but I do not have access to this. I will request the password for this account.

I was incorrect, this has been shared on LastPass. However, authentication for this account also leads to the same problems:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/68423731-9706ed80-0170-11ea-9b65-84cd44a2db93.png)

I will proceed by enquiring with OIT as to who has access to support from Google.
This shall now be tracked by a ticket in SN@P: https://princeton.service-now.com/snap?sys_id=006820ecdbcd849000822a9b8a96199e&view=sp&id=ticket&table=incident

comments.body: This was structured as an independent role given that I was assisting @cwulfman with the development of a Vagrant Box (and Playbook) for deploying PULFA 2.0.

https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/923 was the issue that this was also seeking to advance, but I completely understand the concerns regarding the testing of the Role.  It's a simple task really - should I just duplicate this between the `pulfa` and `plantain` Playbooks @kayiwa and @hackmastera?

> #923 was the issue that this was also seeking to advance, but I completely understand the concerns regarding the testing of the Role. It's a simple task really - should I just duplicate this between the `pulfa` and `plantain` Playbooks @kayiwa and @hackmastera?

I would personally put them as a task in `pulfa` and `plantain` instead of a playbook.
This should just duplicate Subversion checkouts between this new Role and that of `plantain` (hence, https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/pull/933 should remain closed).
